      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "I think that we can choose how we section our brain between these three uses. Storage space is taken up by whatever we are storing and the more we store the more we grow our storage capacity. The rest we can choose to use in either thinking or feeling mode and we can partition (not literally!) our brain between these two uses. When we ride we are mainly in feeling and body control mode. However, we also think and store. The partitioning is, say, 80% feeling and 20% thinking. Then when we are off the horse but thinking about riding in the evening the percentages change to say 20% feeling and 80% thinking.",
